OL,3,CNUFC legend Shaka Hislop reveals
OL,4,C'aggressive' prostate cancer battle
OL,6,FMen aged 50 or over can ask their GP
OL,7,Ffor a PSA test, even if they do not
OL,8,Fhave symptoms. Anyone aged 50 or over
OL,9,Fwith a prostate can ask for a PSA test.
OL,11,FThe UK government website says about
OL,12,F50,000 men each year are diagnosed
OL,13,Fwith prostate cancer and about 12,000
OL,14,Fdie from the disease. More than 75% of
OL,15,Fmen with prostate cancer survive with
OL,16,Fthe disease for 10 or more years.
OL,18,FInformation and support regarding
OL,19,Fprostate cancer and the PSA test can
OL,20,Fbe found on the Prostate Cancer UK
OL,21,Fsite.
